author: WCAX News
title: Police arrest man suspected in burglary spree
text:
BURLINGTON, Vt. - An arrest in Burlington-- and police say the suspect is connected with a streak of break-ins in the city's South End neighborhood.
Investigators picked up Zachary Senna, 30, of Burlington, on outstanding warrants. They say he is the prime suspect in a burglary at Speeder & Earl's and a string of break-ins in Williston.
The South End has seen more than a dozen break-ins in the last month.
Police are still searching for another suspect, William Nelson, 47.
